<br>
Had I known that Bush would declare war on a country and invade and potentially re-instate the draft on shaky intelligence and carefully crafted propoganda and spin, I wouldn't have voted for him. <br>
<br>
I have internal conflicts with supporting a country that does provide my freedom and well-being (for the most part) but actively and outright lies to its constituency in order to foster conflict with another nation.<br>
<br>
That being said, the people who volunteer for service for their country and people that are drafted by luck (bad or otherwise, if it comes to pass), who work and devote their time to defending my country and my freedom, they have my utmost respect and admiration. It is not a job I would voluntarily do because, honestly, I am a coward.<br>
<br>
And if I were to be called, I wouldn't be happy about it, I might exercise the rights my country provides me to criticize the choices of the government, but I would take up arms and perform my required duties. Perhaps, because it goes against my personal values, some would criticize that as also being cowardly... but I digress..<br>
<br>
Frankly, a draft scares the hell out of me. It really shouldn't, because we'd have to be in dire straits before I was even eligible to be called as I've exceeded the age limit for a first-stage draft invocation. But I'm definitely a coward if it means I'm scared as hell to have someone shooting at me. <br>
<br>
It really depends on the perspective... support, criticize, actively work against the nature of a draft, of the military, depending on how you look at it, you could be accurately labelled a coward, either shying away from your personal views, of which you have right to under our constitution, or shying away from patriotic responsibility.<br>
<br>
But one thing's for certain, the folks that are there now, the ones who are being shot at day in and day out are definitely not cowards. Nor are any of the others that have served in peacetime or fought in wars past. <br>
<br>
Owell, back to attempts at witty one-liners.<br>
