Anyone not willing to serve to defend our country should have their citizenship revoked.  I don't give a flying fuck what your politics, your religion, your race:  it's the way its been since the Revolutionary War.<br>
<br>
Do I want to get drafted?  Fuck no.  Do I think THIS war is worth a draft (which tends to mean &quot;its not a &quot;surgical&quot; war anymore - we need rabble to throw into machine gun fire so we keep the highly trained troops alive&quot;)?  Probably not.<br>
<br>
But would I go if my country called?  Your goddamned right.  You have your &quot;rights&quot; off the blood of men and women who answered the call.  Saying one won't do the same means you are unworthy of these rights. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daemuniscariot>Daemun Iscariot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 128<br> <font color=#330000>(7/23/03 7:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=877.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> better to be cautious than dead</span><hr size=1> Elrynia, you're right. not everything IS a govt conspiracy. but the real reasons behind this war are. they tell us one thing and do another, or do something and tell us its for one reason when it is for another. and when they crack a smile behind our backs and we see it, theres always plenty of gullible fucks willing to defend them. i am not one of those. and i have no respect for the ones who are. not everything is a govt conspiracy, but i think it is better, these days, to be cautious and think that perhaps it is, rather than to be complacent, think everything is just fine, and get run around in circles like a good little sheep because of my ignorance. <br>
they lie to us more and more, and i only think we should start recognizing and calling them on their fucking lies. they are OUR govt, we are not THEIR slaves. they are supposed to work for us, and its about time they did that instead of working for themselves using power we let them keep.  <br>
<br>
hangetsu, you make a good point. but honestly, if the people who died for wars defending our country in times past were raised here now, to see our country the way it is now, and to see what we fight for, i dont think they would do any different. if america were the way it is now back in the 1700's, George washington would never have left his farm to come to join the Sons of Liberty, and we would still all be under British rule, being taxed without representation. instead, everything that our country does is without true representation, we ourselves donot decide what we do as a country, a small elite group of people &quot;we&quot; supposedly choose does, when the truth is we have gotten too big for our own ideals. i think if americans are polled and less than 75% of them agree with a given action to be taken by our govt, than it should not be taken. isnt that what representation is about ? but even that would not work. <br>
<br>
i guess i feel a sort of remorse for not having patriotism. i really only wish there was something so wonderful about our country in these times that it would override all the bad and make me WANT to defend it. but the sad truth is, that patriotism is at an all time low. forget the group cocksuck that happened after 9/11 - it is true. many many americans couldnt give a shit about our country or what happens to it, so long as they are allowed to remin comfortable in front of their tv, computer, whatever. i just think it is sad, i can only barely imagine the pride of our founding fathers as they set out to do something unprecedented in human history, and their disappointment in the afterlife now if they only knew that in the end they failed. <br>
<br>
but then again, i'm just a commie bastard, what do i know ? <br>
